Ronald R. Spadafora - McGraw-Hill's Firefighter Exams
Pages:418 | PDF | McGraw-Hill Contemporary; 1 edition (1 Feb 2008) | ISBN 0071477691

The complete, up-to-the-minute guide to firefighter qualifying exams across America-for the thousands of aspiring firefighters who apply each year

Firefighters don't just fight fires anymore-they're also the designated first-responders for nearly any kind of emergency. McGraw-Hill gives you the latest information on all the requirements for fire departments across America. A renowned firefighting expert and trainer, Ronald Spadafora explains the ins and outs to passing the oral interview, the psychological test, the physical ability test, the video-based tests, and the written qualifying exams.
